\fs24 \cf0 \
After the installation, please visit {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://src.opensolaris.org/source/xref/nv-g11n/inputmethod/sunpinyin/ime/data"}}{\fldrslt http://src.opensolaris.org/source/xref/nv-g11n/inputmethod/sunpinyin/ime/data}} to download lm_sc.t3g.le and pydict_sc.bin.le data files (for PowerPC platform, please download the '.be' versions), rename them by eliminating the le/be postfix, then copy them to /Library/Input Methods/SunPinyin.app/Contents/Resources.}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf949\cocoasubrtf430
{\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Monaco;}
{\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;}
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural

\f0\fs24 \cf0 SunPinyin is an opensource'd (in CDDL/LGPLv2.1) and SLM (Statistical Language Model) based input method engine. It uses a trigram back-off language model, to support sentence input.\
\
Currently, it's available on IIIMF, SCIM, BeCJK, and now on Mac OS X (Leopard only).\
\
We are looking for contributors for the input engine itself, and the Mac porting. And you may refer to my {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://blogs.sun.com/yongsun/tags/sunpinyin"}}{\fldrslt sunpinyin}} blog entries for more technical details.}

